values.description: The CA80xx changes from automatic mode to fieldbus mode.
The CA80xx changes from fieldbus  mode to automatic mode continuing with the time schedule as it was calculated when entering  automatic mode, the first time.
The system changes from fieldbus mode to automatic mode and restarts the time schedule with the current time as starting point.

description: This parameter is used to control the active operation mode

group.name: Analyzer Manual Actions
group.description: The following parameters are available to switch into fieldbus mode, which enables the remote control over Modbus function, and to start an action and read back its progress

description: The parameter is used to abort the current activity

group.name: Analyzer Manual Actions
group.description: The following parameters are available to switch into fieldbus mode, which enables the remote control over Modbus function, and to start an action and read back its progress

description: This parameter is used to start an action

values.description: The analyzer is waiting for a request
Writing the parameter “Mode change request” was accepted. Mode change is in progress.
The analyzer is in operation mode that the fieldbus is not allowed to change (like manual mode).

description: This parameter reads the status of the mode change.

group.name: Analyzer manual actions state
group.description: The parameters in the register block 'Analyzer manual actions state' are used to read the status of the status machine.

values.description: No procedure is running. This state is entered, if the analyzer enters fieldbus mode, while nothing is running that disturbs the start of  any function via fieldbus.
The request was accepted, but the requested function is not started yet.
The analyzer is not in fieldbus mode and cannot accept action requests.

description: This parameter reads the status of processing the requested  <function> (Measurement,  Calibration or Cleaning).

group.name: Analyzer manual actions state
group.description: The parameters in the register block 'Analyzer manual actions state' are used to read the status of the status machine.
